ing Downgrade<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=
bsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>ADD<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>INR 1,490</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">Havel=
ls missed 4Q revenue estimate but beat EBITDA/PAT estimates given (1) stron=
ger C&amp;W margin, and (2) lower-than-expected losses in Lloyd despite rev=
enue declining 19% YoY. Within C&amp;W, Havells
 reported ~6% volume growth, with wires (higher share of copper) volume dec=
lining while cables (mix of copper and aluminium) volume rose minimally; in=
creasing price trends aided margin. The company indicated demand has improv=
ed off late in Lloyd after a weak
 start to the summer and inventory may normalise only by end-April. Further=
, within ECD, despite a YoY revenue decline of ~3%, commentary suggested no=
 market share losses. Lastly, on margin, we note a medium-term aspiration t=
o gain 200bps. That said, we build
 in a conservative 100bps expansion over FY26=9629E given (1) Increased inv=
estments in A&amp;P, brand visibility initiatives, and R&amp;D, and (2) unl=
ikelihood of C&amp;W segment margin sustaining as there were gains from ris=
ing input costs in 4Q. We cut our FY27/28E estimates
 by ~3% and value Havells at 45x Mar=9228E EPS, arriving at a TP of INR 1,4=
90, implying ~10% upside to CMP. Hence, downgrade to ADD.</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">&nbsp=
;</span></p>
<div style=3D"border-width:medium medium 1pt; border-style:none none solid;=
 border-color:currentcolor currentcolor silver; padding:0in 0in 1pt">
<p class=3D"EQChapterHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt"=
><a href=3D"https://jmflresearch.com/Download?ReportId=3D21208&amp;Download=
Type=3Dshow"><span lang=3D"EN-IN">SBI Life Insurance | Best bet in an uncer=
tain demand environment</span></a></span></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"EQSubHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">Res=
ult Update<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>BUY<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>INR 2,200</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">SBI L=
ife reported Q4FY26 VNB of INR 16.3bn, &#43;2% JMFe, -2% YoY. Individual AP=
E/total APE growth of 8%/6% YoY was below estimates, while margin surprised=
 positively though it declined 210bps YoY
 to 28.3%. Management had expected a 1.74% full-year impact from GST 2.0 fo=
r this year, but it was lower at 1.50%. FY26 APE growth and margin were in =
line with guidance at 13%/27.5%. Management guided for 14% APE growth and 2=
7=9628% VNB margin for FY27E and the
 near term. We have hardly changed our VNB estimates; we slightly cut APE g=
rowth but raise margin forecasts. We maintain BUY with a revised TP of INR =
2,200, valuing the stock at 1.9x Mar=9228E EVPS of INR 1,158 (against 1.9x =
Mar=9228E EVPS of INR 1,135 earlier).
 March industry volume data and these 4Q results reinforce our view that SB=
I Life is the best play in life insurance (a defensive sector in itself) wh=
en there is demand uncertainty; it remains our top pick in the space.</span=
></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">&nbsp=
;</span></p>
<div style=3D"border-width:medium medium 1pt; border-style:none none solid;=
 border-color:currentcolor currentcolor silver; padding:0in 0in 1pt">
<p class=3D"EQChapterHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt"=
><a href=3D"https://jmflresearch.com/Download?ReportId=3D21209&amp;Download=
Type=3Dshow"><span lang=3D"EN-IN">Tech Mahindra | Inline 4Q results; FY27 m=
argin trajectory remains on track</span></a></span></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"EQSubHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">Res=
ult Update<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>ADD<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>INR 1,555</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">Tech =
Mahindra reported 4QFY26 results =96 revenues and margins were largely inli=
ne. Revenue growth came in at 0.6% cc QoQ vs expectation of 0.4% cc QoQ. EB=
IT margins at 13.8% =96 inline versus JMFL
 and consensus expectations. Forward looking indicators =96 i) LTM new TCV =
grew ~42% YoY in FY26 versus ~43% YoY new TCV growth in FY25 (LTM book to b=
ill of 0.59x in FY26 versus 0.43x in FY25). ii) Headcount saw a slight decl=
ine -1.3% QoQ / -0.7% YoY. iii) Management
 commentary =96 confident of doing better than the industry growth and achi=
eve 15% EBIT margins in FY27. Industry growth is expected to be 2-4% or 3-5=
%. Tech Mahindra has executed well on margins =96 already factored in the v=
aluations, in our view. Valuations are
 at 19x FY27 consensus EPS, at c.7% premium to the sector. We revise our EP=
S estimates marginally over FY27-28E, incorporating 4Q results. Maintain ta=
rget multiple of 19x Sep 27 =96 revised TP of INR 1,555 (versus INR 1,550 e=
arlier). Maintain ADD.</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">&nbsp=
;</span></p>
