 border-color:currentcolor currentcolor silver; padding:0in 0in 1pt">
<p class=3D"EQChapterHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt"=
><a href=3D"https://jmflresearch.com/Download?ReportId=3D21210&amp;Download=
Type=3Dshow"><span lang=3D"EN-IN">Tata Communications | Earnings beat on st=
rong digital portfolio growth</span></a></span></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"EQSubHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">Res=
ult Update<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>BUY<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>INR 1,980</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">Tata =
Communications (TCOM) reported consolidated revenue of INR 65.5bn (up 5.9% =
QoQ and 9.4% YoY) for Q4FY26, higher than JMFe/consensus, led by strong gro=
wth across digital portfolio, core connectivity,
 voice segments and TCR. Data segment revenue was 4.2% higher than JMFe at =
INR 56.8bn (up 6.1% QoQ and 11.5% YoY) as digital portfolio revenue was 6.7=
% higher than JMFe at INR 29.1bn (up 9.4% QoQ and 19.2% YoY) and core conne=
ctivity revenue was also 1.7% higher
 at INR 27.7bn (up 2.8% QoQ and 4.5% YoY). However, consolidated EBITDA, at=
 INR 12.8bn (up 4.5% QoQ and 14.4% YoY), was only 0.9-2.6% higher than JMFe=
/consensus due to higher network and other opex, resulting in EBITDA margin=
 of 19.6% in Q4FY26 (19.8% in 3QFY26).
 Net debt fell QoQ to INR 94bn while capex fell QoQ to INR 5.4bn or 8.3% of=
 revenue in 4Q. We maintain our BUY rating on TCOM (unchanged TP of INR 1,9=
80/share) based on 10x FY28 EV/EBITDA multiple for the data segment (5Y his=
torical average of 11x) as we expect
 data segment EBITDA to grow at a robust CAGR of ~20% over FY26=9629E, driv=
en by a) strong growth in digital portfolio, positioned strongly across key=
 megatrends like cloud, AI, IoT, etc.; b) improvement in overall EBITDA mar=
gin from current ~20% to ~22% by FY28
 (management guidance of 23=9625%) as operating leverage and acquisition sy=
nergies are likely to be partly offset by adverse revenue mix.</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">&nbsp=
;</span></p>
