<p class=3D"EQSubHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">Res=
ult Update<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>BUY<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>INR 560</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">Sunte=
ck Realty (SRL) posted robust FY26 pre-sales of c. INR 31.6bn (&#43;25% YoY=
) with Q4FY26 at c. INR 10.6bn (&#43;22% YoY; &#43;45% QoQ; -4% JMFe), unde=
rpinned by sustained traction in premium and uber-luxury
 segments. Quarterly collections increased 39% YoY to c. INR 4.3bn; for FY2=
6, collections rose 14% YoY to INR 14.3bn with an operating surplus of INR =
5.5bn (&#43;48% YoY). Collections are set to improve meaningfully over FY27=
/FY28 as execution picks up pace. Business
 development accelerated during the year with investments in land increasin=
g to c. INR 8bn (from c. INR 1.8bn in FY25) and the addition of c. INR 50bn=
 GDV across three new projects, with embedded margins of c. 30=9635%. The l=
aunch pipeline remains healthy (c.
 INR 70bn GDV for FY27), including subsequent phases at Vasai and Naigaon a=
longside a recently signed JDA project in Mira Road. The Dubai project is l=
aunch-ready, subject to geopolitical normalisation. Overall, management exp=
resses confidence in sustaining
 current pre-sales momentum into FY27, irrespective of the Dubai project la=
unch. Pre-sales could expand at 27% CAGR over FY26=9628E on the back of mul=
tiple launches. We reiterate BUY with a DCF based Mar=9227E TP of INR 560.<=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">&nbsp=
;</span></p>
