 border-color:currentcolor currentcolor silver; padding:0in 0in 1pt">
<p class=3D"EQChapterHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt"=
><a href=3D"https://jmflresearch.com/Download?ReportId=3D21204&amp;Download=
Type=3Dshow"><span lang=3D"EN-IN">PNC Infratech | Receives much awaited NHA=
I orders; backlog strengthens</span></a></span></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"EQSubHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">Com=
pany Update<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=
p;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>BUY<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>INR 345</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">PNC I=
nfratech (PNC) has been declared L1 by the NHAI in two HAM road projects fo=
r 4-laning of the Barabanki=96Biswariya stretch in Uttar Pradesh; this woul=
d have a total EPC value of c. INR 30bn.
 And given the packages are contiguous, we expect them to support margins. =
These wins are particularly positive as NHAI order inflows had remained slo=
w over the past two years=97 for instance, PNC=92s FY26 inflows aggregated =
INR 60bn versus guidance of INR 120bn.
 Now these fresh wins will strengthen order backlog and improve execution v=
isibility. Order backlog stood at a strong INR 203bn (2.9x TTM revenue) at =
end-Dec-25. All in all, we reckon a robust EPS CAGR of 22% over FY25=9628E.=
 Meanwhile, the stock is trading at
 an attractive 10x/8x FY27E/28E EPS. All in all, our valuation and TP remai=
n unchanged=97we value the EPC business at 13x FY27E EPS yielding an SotP-b=
ased TP of INR 345; maintain BUY.</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">&nbsp=
;</span></p>
