 border-color:currentcolor currentcolor silver; padding:0in 0in 1pt">
<p class=3D"EQChapterHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt"=
><a href=3D"https://jmflresearch.com/Download?ReportId=3D21206&amp;Download=
Type=3Dshow"><span lang=3D"EN-IN">ABB India | Parent reported order inflows=
, which seems largely inline</span></a></span></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"EQSubHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">Fla=
sh Update</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">ABB I=
ndia=92s parent entity ABB Global has reported 1QCY26 numbers with overall =
24% YoY growth in order inflows on a comparable basis (possibly adjusting f=
or sale of Robotics &amp; Automation). A positive
 read-through for India is the reported 1QCY26 order inflow of &#43;26% YoY=
, the highest in the key AMEA region for ABB Global. This appears in-line w=
ith our estimate of INR43bn (preview note) of ~27% YoY order inflow (ex. Ro=
botics) for ABB India in 1QCY26E. That
 said, margins may remain under pressure for ABB India. Moreover, current v=
aluations make the risk reward profile significantly adverse, in our view.<=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">&nbsp=
;</span></p>
<div style=3D"border-width:medium medium 1pt; border-style:none none solid;=
 border-color:currentcolor currentcolor silver; padding:0in 0in 1pt">
<p class=3D"EQChapterHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt"=
><a href=3D"https://jmflresearch.com/Download?ReportId=3D21205&amp;Download=
Type=3Dshow"><span lang=3D"EN-IN">Strategy | JM India Pulse =96 Mar=9226</s=
pan></a></span></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"EQSubHeading"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">Sec=
tor Update</span></p>
<p class=3D"EQBodyText"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10pt">In th=
is note, we lay out the most important monthly market, sectoral and economi=
c indicators tracked by the JM Financial research team. The indicators span=
 high-frequency macro variables and sector-level
 operating metrics that help assess near-term growth momentum and emerging =
inflection points. Escalation in the West Asia conflict sent Brent crude oi=
l price soaring past the USD 100/bbl mark. FII selling intensified and the =
INR weakened; however, the trade
 deficit narrowed in Mar=9226. The domestic environment reflects selective =
strength led by improving discretionary consumption and credit growth amid =
easing financial conditions. Household financialisation remains resilient e=
ven as digital payment growth normalises.
 Industrial activity moderated slightly with capex remaining uneven. Rising=
 oil and gas prices, supply disruptions and geopolitical uncertainty have d=
riven the recent volatility in Indian equity markets, though peace talks be=
tween the US and Iran have improved
 market sentiment.</span></p>
